        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 30 at 11:17PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1117 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Lela, or 4 miles west of Shamrock, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Shamrock, Dozier, Lutie, Lela, Samnorwood, and Twitty.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
